Parliament, Tuesday, 10 September 2019 – The Joint Standing Committee on Financial Management of Parliament will tomorrow, 11 September 2019, be briefed by the Executive Authority of Parliament, in a closed meeting, on the outcome of the Public Service Commission inquiry into the tragic death of Mr Lennox Garane in September 2018. It will also be briefed, in a meeting open to the public, on the progress regarding the disciplinary proceedings against the Secretary to Parliament, Mr Gengezi Mgidlana. The Executive Authority of Parliament consist of the Speaker of the National Assembly, Ms Thandi Modise and Deputy Speaker Mr Lechesa Tsenoli, as well as Chairperson of the National Council of Provinces, Mr Amos Masondo and Deputy Chairperson Ms Sylvia Lucas. Details of the meeting are as follows:
	Venue: Committee Room M514, Fifth Floor, Marks Building
	Time: 13:00-14:00 ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CO-CHAIRPERSONS OF THE JOINT STANDING COMMITTEE ON FINANCIAL MANAGEMENT OF PARLIAMENT, MS GLADYS MAHLANGU AND MS PEACE MABE. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Mr Justice Molafo
	Tel: 021 403 8444
	Cell: 081 424 7481
	Email: jmolafo@parliament.gov.za   Anybody over the age of 18 can participate indirectly in Parliament simply by voting in the elections.Read more